ivardefs.name: identifier_
ivardefs.desc: This records identifiers associated with this biologically derived product instance that are defined by business processes and/or used to refer to it when a direct URL reference to the resource itself is not appropriate (e.g. in CDA documents, or in writt

ivardefs.name: manipulation
ivardefs.desc: Any manipulation of product post-collection that is intended to alter the product.  For example a buffy-coat enrichment or CD8 reduction of Peripheral Blood Stem Cells to make it more suitable for infusion.

ivardefs.name: processing_
ivardefs.desc: Any processing of the product during collection that does not change the fundamental nature of the product. For example adding anti-coagulants during the collection of Peripheral Blood Stem Cells.

ivardefs.name: productCode
ivardefs.desc: A code that identifies the kind of this biologically derived product (SNOMED Ctcode).

ivardefs.name: quantity
ivardefs.desc: Number of discrete units within this product.

ivardefs.name: request_
ivardefs.desc: Procedure request to obtain this biologically derived product.

ivardefs.name: status
ivardefs.desc: Whether the product is currently available.

properties.desc:
A material substance originating from a biological entity intended to be transplanted or infused
into another (possibly the same) biological entity.
